<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1455948>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–2. Prosternum in male: 1 Drymadusa dorsalis grandis; 2 Parapholidoptera antaliae; 3–4. Fastigium of vertex in female: 3 Anadolua burri; 4 Tettigonia caudata; 5 Tettigonia caudata male habitus lateral view; 6–7. Fastigium of vertex in male: 6 Drymadusa dorsalis grandis; 7 Phytodrymadusa miramae; 8–9. Gampsocleis recticauda: 8 male fastigium of vertex; 9 male plantula and metatarsus; 10 female plantula and metatarsus of Anadrymadusa (s.str.) adzharica; 11–12. Male pronotum, dorsal view: 11 Drymadusa dorsalis grandis; 12 Novadrymadusa karabagi; 13–14. Male habitus lateral view: 13 Drymadusa dorsalis grandis; 14 Novadrymadusa karabagi; 15–18. Male end of abdomen: 15 Anadrymadusa (s.str.) adzharica; 16 Pezodrymadusa striolata; 17 Paradrymadusa brevicerca; 18 Scotodrymadusa turcica." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1455948/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1455952>
    dc:description "FIGURES 38–58. Ovipositor: 38 Scotodrymadusa maculata; 39 Mixodusa retusa sp. nov.; 40–41. Female habitus lateral view: 40 Anadolua schwarzi; 41 Phytodrymadusa miramae; 42–45. Titillators: 42 Scotodrymadusa turcica; 43 Mixodusa retusa sp. nov.; 44 Phytodrymadusa miramae; 45 Leptodusa expugnata; 46–47. Male habitus lateral view: 46 Lithodusa helverseni (from Heller & Korsunovskaya 2009); 47 Leptodusa expugnata; 48 Phytodrymadusa miramae, male end of abdomen; 49 Phytodrymadusa miramae, female pronotum and tegmina, dorso-lateral view; 50–51. Leptodusa expugnata: 50 male last tergite; 51 male cercus; 52–53. Mixodusa retusa sp. nov.: 52 male last tergite, 53 male cercus; 54–55. Female pronotum and tegmina: 54 Leptodusa harzi; 55 Mixodusa retusa sp. nov.; 56–57. End of hind tibia, ventral view: 56 Decticus albifrons female; 57 Rhacocleis turcica male; 58 Psorodonotus caucasicus, female fore tibia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1455952/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1455950>
    dc:description "FIGURES 19–37. Habitus lateral view: 19 Pezodrymadusa striolata, male; 20 Pezodrymadusa lata, female; 21 Anadrymadusa (s.str.) adzharica, male; 22 ditto female; 23–24. Novadrymadusa karabagi: 23 male end of abdomen; 24 female 7th sternite and subgenital plate; 25 Anadolua burri, male end of abdomen; 26 Mixoduda retusa sp. nov. 7th sternite and subgenital plate; 27–29. Frons in male: 27 Paradrymadusa aksirayi; 28 Scotodrymadusa turcica; 29 Mixodusa retusa sp. nov.; 30–31. Male end of abdomen: 30 Paradrymadusa aksirayi; 31 Anadolua schwarzi; 32–37. Ovipositor: 32, 33 Anadolua schwarzi; 34, 35, 36 Anadolua burri; 37 Scotodrymadusa turcica." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1455950/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1455966>
    dc:description "FIGURES 186–203. Habitus lateral view: 186 Sureyaella bella, male; 187 ditto female; 188 Anterastes burri, male; 189 ditto female; 190 Koroglus disparalatus, male; 191 ditto female; 192–193. Male tegmina and pronotum, dorsal view: 192 Anterastes serbicus; 193 Koroglus disparalatus; 194–195. Anterastes babadaghi: 194 male left tegmen, inner surface; 195 ditto stridulatory file area; 196–197. Koroglus disparalatus: 196 male left tegmen, inner surface; 197 ditto stridulatory file area; 198–203. Mixodusa retusa sp. nov.: 198 male habitus, lateral view; 199 male head, pronotum and tegmina, lateral view; 200 ditto dorsal view; 201 male last tergite and cerci; 202 male subgenital plate; 203 female habitus, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1455966/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1455954>
    dc:description "FIGURES 59–80. Fore tibia in female: 59 Bucephaloptera bucephala; 60 Platycleis (Montana) taurica; 61 Parapholidoptera antaliae; 62–63. Pronotum and fore femur in male: 62 Psorodonotus caucasicus; 63 Bucephaloptera bucephala; 64–66. Male end of abdomen: 64 Bucephaloptera bucephala; 65 Decticus verrucivorus verrucivorus; 66 Medecticus assimilis; 67–68. Male habitus, lateral view: 67 Festella festae; 68 Medecticus assimilis; 69–70. Female subgenital plate: 69 Bucephaloptera bucephala; 70 Festella festae; 71 titillators of Bucephaloptera bucephala; 72–73. Male pronotum: 72 Decticus albifrons; 73 Medecticus assimilis; 74–77. Pronotum and tegmina: 74 Platycleis (Montana) uvarovi, male; 75 ditto female; 76 Pholidoptera griseoaptera, male; 77 ditto female; 78–80. Male tegmina: 78 Platycleis (s.str.) escalerai; 79 Metrioptera (Roeseliana) bispina; 80 Sepiana sepium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1455954/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1455956>
    dc:description "FIGURES 81–105. Sepiana sepium: 81 male pronotum; 82 male end of abdomen; 83 female 6th, 7th sternites and subgenital plate; 84–86. Metrioptera (Roeseliana) bispina: 84 male pronotum; 85 male end of abdomen; 86 female 6th, 7th sternites and subgenital plate; 87–88. Platycleis (Platycleis) intermedia: 87 female habitus, lateral view; 88 female 7th sternite and subgenital plate; 89–90. Platycleis (Montana) uvarovi: 89 female habitus, lateral view; 90 female 7th sternite and subgenital plate; 91–92. Male tegmina and body, lateral view: 91 Platycleis (Tessellana) nigrosignata; 92 Platycleis (Squamiana) kurmana; 93–97. Female habitus, lateral view: 93 Platycleis (Montana) elegans; 94 Platycleis (Incertana) incerta; 95 Platycleis (Incertana) persica; 96 Platycleis (Tessellana) nigrosignata; 97 Platycleis (Tessellana) veyseli; 98–99. Male pronotum and tegmina: 98 Platycleis (Incertana) incerta; 99 Platycleis (Tessellana) nigrosignata; 100–101. Platycleis (Incertana) persica: 100 titillators; 101 female subgenital plate; 102–103. Platycleis (Tessellana) nigrosignata: 102 titillators; 103 female subgenital plate; 104–105. Platycleis (Yalvaciana) yalvaci, habitus lateral view: 104 male; 105 female." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1455956/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1455958>
    dc:description "FIGURES 106–129. Platycleis (Yalvaciana) yalvaci: 106 male last tergite; 107 male cercus; 108 female subgenital plate; 109–111. Platycleis (Sporadiana) sporadarum: 109 male last tergite; 110 male cercus; 111 female subgenital plate; 112–115. Platycleis (Squamiana) sinuata: 112 male last tergite; 113 male cercus; 114 female subgenital plate; 115 ovipositor; 116 Platycleis (Sporadiana) sporadarum, ovipositor; 117–119. Metrioptera (Broughtonia) arnoldi: 117 head and pronotum (from Sevgili et al. 2011); 118 male body lateral view (from Cigliano et al. 2018); 119 male subgenital plate (from Sevgili et al. 2011); 120–121. Metrioptera (Bicolorana) bicolor: 120 male subgenital plate; 121 male habitus lateral view (120 and 121 from Cigliano et al. 2018); 122–125. Metrioptera (Roeseliana) bispina: 122 male pronotum and tegmina; 123 male end of abdomen; 124 female subgenital plate; 125 female habitus, lateral view; 126–129. Metrioptera (Vichetia) oblongicollis: 126 male pronotum and tegmina; 127 male end of abdomen; 128 female subgenital plate; 129 female habitus, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1455958/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1455960>
    dc:description "FIGURES 130–145. 130a–f. Male habitus, dorsal view: a Pachytrachis gracilis; b Bolua turkiyae; c Rammeola anatolica; d Pholidoptera brevipes; e Parapholidoptera belen; f Eupholidoptera smyrnensis; 131–133. Rammeola anatolica: 131 male end of abdomen; 132 male cercus; 133 female subgenital plate and 7th sternite; 134–135. Pachytrachis gracilis: 134 male end of abdomen; 135 female subgenital plate and 7th sternite; 136–137. Bolua turkiyae: 136 male end of abdomen; 137 female subgenital plate and 7th sternite; 138–139. Rammeola anatolica habitus, lateral view: 138 male; 139 female; 140–141. Pachytrachis gracilis habitus, lateral view: 140 male; 141 female; 142–143. Bolua turkiyae habitus, lateral view: 142 male; 143 female; 144–145. Male end of abdomen: 144 Pholidoptera fallax; 145 Parapholidoptera spinulosa." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1455960/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1455962>
    dc:description "FIGURES 146–166. Male end of abdomen: 146 Apholidoptera pietschmanni; 147 Eupholidoptera anatolica; 148 Uvarovistia satunini; 149 Exopholidoptera brevifemora; 150–152. Male pronotum and tegmina, dorso-lateral view: 150 Pholidoptera aptera bulgarica; 151 Parapholidoptera antaliae; 152 Apholidoptera pietschmanni; 153 Pholidoptera femorata, male end of abdomen; 154–156. Female hind femur, outer surface: 154 Apholidoptera pietschmanni; 155 Parapholidoptera grandis; 156 Parapholidoptera syriaca; 157–158. Eupholidoptera akdeniz: 157 male end of abdomen; 158 male habitus, lateral view; 159–160. Uvarovistia zebra: 159 male end of abdomen; 160 male habitus, lateral view; 161 Exopholidoptera brevifemora, male habitus, lateral view; 162–166. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view: 162 Eupholidoptera akdeniz; 163 Uvarovistia zebra; 164 Uvarovistia satunini; 165 ditto lateral view; 166 Exopholidoptera brevifemora." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1455962/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1455964>
    dc:description "FIGURES 167–185. Exopholidoptera brevifemora: 167 male head and pronotum, lateral view; 168 female head and pronotum, dorsal view; 169 Uvarovistia satunini female head and pronotum, dorsal view; 170–173. Female habitus, lateral view: 170 Eupholidoptera smyrnensis; 171 Uvarovistia satunini; 172 Uvarovistia zebra; 173 Exopholidoptera brevifemora; 174–175. Female hind femur, outer surface: 174 Uvarovistia satunini; 175 Exopholidoptera brevifemora; 176–179. Male frons: 176 Rhacocleis germanica; 177 Sureyaella bella; 178 Anterastes serbicus; 179 Koroglus disparalatus; 180–181. Plantula and metatarsus: 180 Rhacocleis germanica; 181 Anterastes burri; 182–185. Male end of abdomen: 182 Rhacocleis germanica; 183 Sureyaella bella; 184 Anterastes burri; 185 Koroglus disparalatus." ;
